===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}} вҖ“ a figure leaning forward, presumably running, hence energetic, young. See also the top component of the Kangxi radical [[иө°]].

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Coblin (1986)}} (apud {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}) considers it cognate to {{cog|bo|аҪЎаҪјајӢаҪ–||oblique, aslant}}, {{m|bo|аҪӮаҪЎаҪјајӢаҪ–||tilt}}, {{m|bo|аҪӮаҪЎаҪјаҪҰ}}; if so, probably of {{der|zh|sit}} origin. However, the medials do not agree, as the expected Middle Chinese reflex should be in division IV, not III-B ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare also {{cog|lus|eu||to bend backwards}} (ibid.).

Possibly related to {{och-l|е§”|id=2|to bend}} (e.g. in {{w|Chuci}} [https://ctext.org/chu-ci/yuan-you1?searchu=%E5%A7%94&searchmode=showall#result]) (ibid.).

